The United States has expressed deep concern over recent attacks on civilian centers in the Central African Republic (CAR), including an attack on a Christian church and retaliatory attacks on Muslim community members. The US urges the CAR government to ensure the safety and security of all citizens, regardless of their faith, and calls for professionalism from CAR's security forces in dealing with ongoing security challenges. The US also supports the United Nations mission in CAR in their efforts to protect civilians. Additionally, the US calls on the citizens of CAR to reject violence and hatred, particularly from armed groups seeking to exploit the situation for their own gain. The US expresses its support for the people of CAR and their elected government in their pursuit of better security, peace, and prosperity.